Davis.KSFM:
KSFM (102.5 FM) is a Rhythmic Contemporary Hits radio station serving Sacramento, California. Its city of license and transmitter are located in Woodland in Yolo County but the studios and offices are 5345 Madison Avenue in Sacramento. KSFM is owned by Entercom, which in turn is part of the company's Sacramento cluster, which includes KKDO, KSEG, KRXQ, KUDL, and KIFM.
KSFM's previous slogan was "Sacramento's #1 Station for Hip-Hop and R&B" from 2006 to 2010, when it changed its slogan to just "1025" with a broadened mix on R&B/Hip-Hop and Rhythmic Pop product.
